Curve definition
----------------
"nufloor-Xe.txt" contains the Xenon SI neutrino floor as defined in
O'Hare (2021) PRL: the discovery limit (σ at which a 2-event signal from
neutrino backgrounds appears), which corresponds to the "fog gradient n=2"
definition (Eq. 14 of arXiv:2109.03116).

Used in paper 2506.19062 (Arcadi, Profumo): Fig. 6/7 show the O'Hare 2021
Xenon SI neutrino floor as the benchmark floor curve.

Usage in /ddcalc
----------------
opt-in via `--nu-floor ohare_2021`.
Default source remains DDCalc built-in (ddcalc_builtin_2.2.0).
